      "source": [
        "# Phase 4: Flight Delay Prediction Modeling\n",
        "\n",
        "**Course:** COMP4381 Data Science\n",
        "\n",
        "This notebook implements a **two-stage flight delay prediction system** at the airport-day level, built on top of the Phase 3 cleaned dataset:\n",
        "\n",
        "- **Stage 1 — Classification (Logistic Regression):** *Will an airport-day be delayed (15+ minutes) or not?* (`target_delayed_15`)\n",
        "- **Stage 2 — Regression (Linear Regression):** *How many minutes will the delay be?* (`target_delay_minutes`)\n",
        "\n",
        "The notebook is fully **standalone**: it loads the Phase 3 cleaned CSV directly and runs end-to-end. It covers data loading, leakage prevention, train/test splitting, preprocessing, model training, and evaluation for both stages, using only techniques covered in class."
      ]
    },
